You're right about the community property.  I said half, but that's a
mistake.  A spouse can, in a will, give half of the community property
to someone other than the other spouse.  But if there's no will the
other spouse gets it all.

If there are two or more kids the surviving spouse gets one-third of
the separate property, not half.  See Cal. Probate Code §6401.

